Last Name: Percy
	

   1. English (of Norman origin): habitational name from any of various places in northern France, 
so called from the Gallo-Roman personal name Persius + the locative suffix -acum. 
The suggestion has also been made that it is a nickname from Old French perce(r) ‘to pierce or breach’ + haie ‘hedge’, 
‘enclosure’, referring either to a soldier remembered for his breach of a fortification, 
or in jest to a poacher who was in the habit of breaking into a private park.

	Dictionary of American Family Names, Oxford University Press, ISBN 0-19-508137-4